B.VS=new A.q(!0,B.b_,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,1.6,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
B.YL=new A.cD("  AETHERIS GLOBAL SOLUTIONS\nCorporate Travel & Expense Compliance Manual\nVersion: 2026.04.1-B\nClassification: Internal / Highly Confidential\n\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\n1 Article I: Purpose, Scope, and Employee Responsibility\n2 Article II: Definitions and Interpretations\n3 Article III: Expense Classification Framework\n4 Article IV: Subsistence and Meal Allowances\n5 Article V: Transportation and Logistics\n6 Article VI: Accommodation and Lodging\n7 Article VII: High-Risk Expenditures and Temporal Clauses\n8 Article VIII: Ethical Compliance and Conduct\n9 Article IX: Receipt, Documentation, and Digital Evidence\n10 Article X: AI Audit Engine and Enforcement Protocol\n11 Article XI: Exceptions, Escalations, and Appeals\n12 Article XII: Regional Annexes\n13 Article XIII: Compliance Violations\n14 Appendices A\u2013C\n\nARTICLE I: PURPOSE AND SCOPE\nSection 1.1: Objective\nThis policy establishes a comprehensive framework to ensure financial discipline, transparency,\nand compliance across all expense-related activities within the organization. It is designed to\nstandardize reimbursement practices and minimize misuse of corporate funds.\nSection 1.2: Applicability\nThis policy applies universally across the organization, covering all categories of employees and\nassociated personnel.\n1 Full-time employees\n2 Part-time employees\n3 Contractors and consultants\n4 Executive leadership\nSection 1.3: Employee Responsibility\nAll claimants are expected to uphold the highest standards of integrity while submitting expense\nclaims.\n1 Ensure accuracy and truthfulness of claims\n2 Provide complete and verifiable documentation\n3 Act in the best financial interest of the company\nSection 1.4: Enforcement Authority\nAll expense submissions are evaluated by an automated AI Audit Engine, ensuring consistency and\neliminating bias, with optional human review where required.\n\nARTICLE II: DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATIONS\nSection 2.1: Key Definitions\n1 Reimbursable Expense: Valid business-related cost compliant with policy\n2 Non-Reimbursable Expense: Any cost outside defined rules\n3 High-Risk Expense: Expense flagged due to timing or irregularities\n4 Tier-1 City: High-cost global cities listed in annex\nSection 2.2: Interpretation Rules\n1 Strictest interpretation applies in ambiguity\n2 Currency must follow official conversion rules\n3 AI interpretation prevails unless overridden\n\nARTICLE III: EXPENSE CLASSIFICATION\nAll expenses must be categorized correctly to ensure accurate validation and compliance.\n1 Meals & Subsistence\n2 Transportation\n3 Accommodation\n4 Client Engagement\n5 Miscellaneous Expenses\nEach category includes defined limits, required justification, and validation checks.\n\nARTICLE IV: MEAL ALLOWANCES\nMeal reimbursements are controlled to prevent excessive spending while ensuring employee\nwell-being.\n1 Standard daily limit: $20 USD\n2 Tier-1 cities: $50 USD\n3 Breakfast \u2264 20%, Lunch \u2264 40%, Dinner \u2264 40%\n4 Alcohol prohibited unless exception applies\n5 Multiple receipts aggregated per day\n\nARTICLE V: TRANSPORTATION\nTransportation costs must be economical and justifiable.\n1 Economy class flights only\n2 Business class allowed for long-haul flights with approval\n3 Standard rail class preferred\n4 Luxury ride tiers prohibited\n5 Trip limit: $500 without approval\n\nARTICLE VI: ACCOMMODATION\n1 Tier-1: $250/night\n2 Tier-2: $150/night\n3 Business hotels allowed\n4 Resorts and personal stays not reimbursable\n\nARTICLE VII: HIGH-RISK EXPENDITURE\nCertain temporal conditions automatically increase risk level.\n1 Weekend expenses flagged\n2 Holiday expenses treated as high risk\n3 Keyword justification required\n\nARTICLE VIII: ETHICAL COMPLIANCE\n1 Gifts above $25 prohibited\n2 Alcohol not reimbursable for personal use\n3 Client events require at least two external attendees\n\nARTICLE IX: DOCUMENTATION\n1 Receipts must include merchant, date, amount, currency\n2 OCR validation required\n3 Submission within 30 days\n4 Invalid receipts rejected\n\nARTICLE X: AI AUDIT ENGINE\n1 Approved, Flagged, Rejected classification\n2 Evaluation based on rules and context\n3 Each decision includes explanation\n\nARTICLE XI: EXCEPTIONS\n1 Manager approval required\n2 Appeals within 7 days\n3 Finance team review\n\nARTICLE XII: REGIONAL ANNEX\n1 Tier-1: New York, London, San Francisco, Zurich, Singapore\n2 Tier-2: All other cities\n\nARTICLE XIII: VIOLATIONS\n1 Minor: warning or denial\n2 Major: penalties or escalation\n3 Fraud: termination and legal action\n\nAPPENDICES\nAppendix A: Sample claims illustrate valid and invalid scenarios.\nAppendix B: Keyword validation ensures correct classification.\nAppendix C: Currency conversion must follow official FX rates.\n  ",null,B.VS,null,null,null,null,null,null,null)
